H. Lynn Harton, Banking


  








ProfileLinks 











H. Lynn Harton
Chief Operating Officer, UCBI
Banking




									Blue Ridge, 									GA, 									US								




 

H. Lynn Harton
Hi, I am H. Lynn Harton, seasoned southeastern banking professional. 

H. Lynn Harton, originally from Asheboro, NC, now makes his home in Greenville, SC.  He has been active in leadership of several banks in the southeast, with particular expertise in risk management and change management.  


H. Lynn Harton's Background
H. Lynn Harton's Experience

Director, President, and Chief Operating Officer at United Community Banks, Inc.September 2012 - Present | Greenville, SC
EVP, Head of Commercial Banking, South at TD Bank GroupSeptember 2010 - June 2011Led the successful integration of TSFG into TD Bank, demonstrated by strong performance in deposit generation, pricing discipline and credit results thru systems conversion.  Client and employee retention was exceptional thru the conversion period.

Also led the legacy TD commercial banking organizations in Florida and the Metro DC areas.
President and CEO at The South Financial GroupFebruary 2007 - February 2011As CEO of TSFG, crafted a dual strategy of "weathering the storm", and "rebuilding the business" in order to focus and direct teammates during a period of intense change and a difficult environment.  Streamlined the organizational structure, refocused objectives, and aligned incentives throughout the organization.  Recruited a team to build a leading SBA business, expanded mortgage originations, increased loan pricing, built liquidity and reduced operating expenses significantly.  

Ultimately successfully negotiated the sale of the company to TD Bank in one of the first non-failed bank transactions since the onset of the credit crisis.
Chief Credit Officer at Regions Financial Corporation, Birmingham AL2004 - 2006Chosen to lead the credit organization as part of the merger between Regions Financial and Union Planters Corporation.  Maintained the strong credit culture of the legacy Regions organization while successfully instituting new processes (centralized collections, special assets, signature commercial approval systems, centralized small business approval) to improve risk management.   Improvements in credit costs were a significant factor in meeting and / or beating earnings estimates for six quarters in a row.
Chief Credit Officer at Union Planters BankJune 2003 - May 2004Recruited to lead the transformation of credit processes and improvement in credit results at Union Planters.  Upgraded talent, rebuilt credit processes, significantly improved risk reporting and analytics.  Divested several high risk lines of business and ultimately significantly improved credit results.
EVP at BB&TJanuary 1983 - June 2003Long record of expanding responsibility and leading change at BB&T in various roles.  Following completion of the management development program, served in various line and risk roles, including: manager of the Management Development Program; Business Services Manager in Graham and in Cary, NC; Regional Loan Administrator for Triad, SC and Corporate Banking; and Head of Business Banking. 
H. Lynn Harton's Education

Wake Forest University1979 – 1983BSBA 
H. Lynn Harton's Interests & Activities

H. Lynn Harton enjoys golf, and travels extensively. 










